snippet.title: How internet communication works: Network Coding
snippet.description:
Information Theory Society presents a brief history of internet communication and packet switched networks leading to the idea of network coding. 

Paper featured in this video: Network Information Flow - http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download;jsessionid=F8130EA435749A8E44E666D09CCCDC8D?doi=10.1.1.534.2207&rep=rep1&type=pdf
